README local-only mentions: 3:BuildingAgent is currently a local development vertical slice: a Fastify API plus a React/Vite Web UI that exercise seeded authentication, project membership, and project-scoped chat.
5:## S01 local run
9:Production auth and SSO are out of scope for this slice. There are no anonymous Web or API paths beyond `/health`; use one of the local seeded accounts:
13:| Ada Lovelace | `ada@example.test` | `local-dev-password` | `Alpha Build` read/write, `Beta Build` read-only |
14:| Grace Hopper | `grace@example.test` | `local-dev-password` | `Gamma Build` read/write |
16:Seeded bearer tokens exist only for local fixture behavior and should not be logged or reused for production auth.
26:The API runs on `http://127.0.0.1:3000` by default. The Web app runs through Vite and proxies `/api` and `/health` to the local API. To point the browser client at a different API origin, set `VITE_API_BASE_URL` for the Web dev server.
